Qualitative results. 
Looking into the annotations and predictions, we see that statements such as ``Final Fantasy VII is developed by Square`` are almost literally included in corresponding evidence links such as Wikipedia pages\footnote{\url{https://en.Wikipedia.org/wiki/Final\_Fantasy\_VII}}. In contrast, relations like nativeLanguage include statements only implicitly, e.g. the native language of ``Marcus Adams`` is never mentioned explicitly in the corresponding Wikipedia page\footnote{\url{https://en.Wikipedia.org/wiki/Marcus\_Adams\_(Canadian\_football)}}.